column5: I doubt we would see some float plane action here but the that one is AWESOME! pretty cool. even on a computer screen makes the hair on the back of your neck stand up. i was in northern england climbing what they call mountains and 2 harrier jets ripped thru the valley a couple of hundred feet below us. almost blew us off the rock when they passed us!
Show them up Wayne.YOU CAN DO IT.   Great find. TFS.

Striding Edge in the Lake District? Had a Tornado go past at the same level up there - v.cool  More plane shenanigans...  http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hvDDDKnNhuE  I give up trying to make the viewer thingie work

The Blue Angel in the last shot going supersonic under the goldengate bridge... blew the windows out of many of the boats watching the airshow. It was his last performance before retirement, but he still took a lot of crap for that.
I wish that commercial passenger jets would fly that low.  It would sure make the flight a lot more fun.
Your camera better be ready the first time.  I'd love a chance to do that... my camera bag does have room for a spare pair of shorts.

NUTS.  I was fishing a small inland lake in western new york about 7 years ago (chautaqua lake) and was out on the water one morning when a Military jet (F-14/15 no idea lol) came down just above the lake and banked hard. At first i was like WOW that was awesome.........and after thinking about if for a bit it kinda ticked me off lol.  Not only did he probably shut the fishing off for the entire day, but his look at me stunt could have gone really wrong.  I just found it really peculiar
Video number 1, at the begining you can see a seagull or pelican falling out of the sky... great video's
